{
  "texts": [
    "This has led to the observation that compute-optimal model shape often matters more than sheer parameter count (Alabdulmohsin et al., 2023), though the underlying mechanisms remain unclear.",
    "Related work has reported symptoms consistent with depth inefficiency, including attention collapse (Zhou et al., 2021), low-pass filtering (Wang et al., 2022), and spectral rank collapse in deep networks (Saada et al., 2024).",
    "A complementary line of work shows that many tokens can be pruned (Rao et al., 2021) and that final layers often exhibit near-zero activations, suggesting that some of these layers can be removed with limited impact on performance (Zhao et al., 2024).",
    "We argue that our Information Scrambling Index provides a common operational lens on these observations, and is consistent with interpreting them as arising from breakdowns in computational strategy rather than from irreducible limitations of depth alone in this regime.",
    "Layer-wise Mechanics and Architectural Assumptions."
  ]
}